description: "Global rules for Artspectiv Studio — static site, trust, git safety, UK English."
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

## Product truth

- **Static site only** — `index.html` is the application. No framework unless explicitly approved.
- **Pricing:** Starter from £445, Monthly from £945, Campaign from £1,595. No legacy £225/£695/£1,095.
- **CTA copy:** "Request a content shoot" — do not genericise.
- **Deploy:** Cloudflare Pages, no build command, output `/`.

## Engineering discipline

- Minimal diffs; match existing CSS token and section patterns in `index.html`.
- UK English in comments, docs, and user-facing explanations.
- No secrets in repo; use `.env.example` patterns only if env is ever added.

## Git safety

- No force-push to `main`, no hard reset, no hook skipping unless user asked.
- Commits only when the user requests them.

## Progressive disclosure

Deep guidance lives in **`.cursor/skills/`** — Read on demand:

- Design: `designing-beautiful-websites`, `ui-ux-pro-max`
- Deploy: `artspectiv-deploy`
- Memory: `artspectiv-memory`
- Verification: `verification-before-completion`

## Performance

- No heavy JS dependencies for simple UI.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (already in `index.html`).
- Images under `assets/` with compression per `docs/image-shot-list.md`.
